### Tender Notice for Bath Institution Temporary Construction Zone

**Reference Number**: WS3976625188
**Date**: 25 April 2023
**Closing Date**: 11 May 2023, 14:00 hours

**Project Description**

Public Works and Government Services Canada, Real Property Branch, is seeking a contractor to design and construct a temporary construction zone (TCZ) at Bath Institution, Kingston, Ontario. This is a prerequisite for the construction of a new 96-bed living unit project.

**Tender Details**

* Bidding is open to all qualified contractors.
* The tender is governed by the Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA).
* The procurement method is competitive, open bidding.
* The contracting authority is Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC).
* The trade opening is Canada-wide.

**Submission Requirements**

* All supporting documentation and bids must be submitted on or before 14:00 hours on 11 May 2023.
* Late submissions will be deemed non-responsive.

**Technical Specifications and Contract Terms**

* The contractor must complete the work by 31 March 2024.
* The construction zone will be designed and built to meet the requirements of the Correctional Service Canada.

**Contact and Additional Information**

* Contact Person: Sheila Dhanna, PSPC (she.lla.dhanna@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca)
* Further information and documents can be accessed through the Ariba Discovery portal (http://discovery.ariba.com/rfx/16085232?extsite=MTYwODUyMzJfQU4wMTQ4NDA1MDk5Mg==).

**Note**: This revised text has been rephrased to improve clarity and professionalism, while retaining the essential information.
